<br>
Up until around level 20, it's a fine weapon that is wonderful for young monks to use.<br>
<br>
I personally have never liked it, because, I see way too many monks hanging on to it long after they should. For instance, there's very little reason for a level 42 monk to be keeping that in a bag for H2H skill ups, when bare fists are just fine in that situation.<br>
<br>
In your case, your damage is going on about the normal clip. Until you get a weapons upgrade, such as a CoT or a Fighting Baton, it may get harder to solo some of the monsters you want to kill.<br>
<br>
But hey, get out there, make some new friends, group up and watch those same monsters die really, really fast.<br>
<br>
-Wubao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ukelwan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelwan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/16/02 10:46:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1605.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hits point Question</span><hr size=1> Also there is a damage-cap until you reach lev 20. After that you will see your damage go up quite a bit. <p><font face="Gill Sans MT"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=70469 target=_blank><font size=3 color="3300ff">Jondalar Fairfist</font></A><br>
