<br>
A Polished Steel Ulak is unaffected by the Damage Cap.<br>
<br>
What the Damage Cap does is limit the effectiveness of high damage weapons in the hands of low level characters. It imposes a maximum value on the Damage rating (which you see when you right-click on the weapon) of the weapon used to calculate actual damage. <br>
<br>
At Level 1-9, the maximum weapon Damage rating used is 10 - already higher than a PSU.<br>
<br>
At Level 10-19, the maximum weapon Damage rating ised is 14.<br>
<br>
At Level 20-29, the maximum weapon damage rating used is soemwhere in the mid to high 20s.<br>
<br>
At Level 30+, there is no Damage cap that anyone has detected.<br>
<br>
When he reaches Level 20, his damage output with a PSU will not change other than what he gains from the few points of increased skill (and any +STR items/buffs he obtains). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=naraz>Naraz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/17/02 6:17:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1605.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hits point Question</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the input guys.  I ding 20 last night and have 300 pp any suggestions on what I could buy for a weapons up grade with that would be appr.<br>
